🧠 The general principle

Better models → better predictions → better outcomes

Where this is used constructively:

* Designing products people actually enjoy
* Explaining things in ways people understand
* Recommending content that’s relevant
* Planning services that meet real needs

That’s the healthy side: alignment with people, not control over them.

⸻

⚖️ Important boundary (this matters more than it seems)

There are two paths that look similar but aren’t:

🟢 Alignment (good)

* Helps people get what they already want
* Transparent or at least non-deceptive
* Preserves choice

🔴 Manipulation (not good)

* Pushes people toward outcomes they wouldn’t choose
* Exploits blind spots or emotional vulnerabilities
* Removes or distorts agency

The same “modeling skill” can be used for either—so the constraint matters.

